{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":739,"text":"So it's 2006."},{"time":2769,"text":"My friend Harold Ford calls me."},{"time":4899,"text":"He's running for U.S. Senate in Tennessee,"},{"time":8564,"text":"and he says, \"Mellody, I desperately need some national press. Do you have any ideas?\""},{"time":13151,"text":"So I had an idea. I called a friend"},{"time":15130,"text":"who was in New York"},{"time":16282,"text":"at one of the most successful\nmedia companies in the world,"},{"time":19671,"text":"and she said, \"Why don't we host"},{"time":21757,"text":"an editorial board lunch for Harold?"},{"time":24003,"text":"You come with him.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":25598,"text":"Harold and I arrive in New York."},{"time":27343,"text":"We are in our best suits."},{"time":29358,"text":"We look like shiny new pennies."},{"time":31573,"text":"And we get to the receptionist, and we say,"},{"time":34094,"text":"\"We're here for the lunch.\""},{"time":35474,"text":"She motions for us to follow her."},{"time":37678,"text":"We walk through a series of corridors,"},{"time":40120,"text":"and all of a sudden we find ourselves"},{"time":41374,"text":"in a stark room,"},{"time":43040,"text":"at which point she looks at us and she says,"},{"time":46130,"text":"\"Where are your uniforms?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":50415,"text":"Just as this happens,"},{"time":51661,"text":"my friend rushes in."},{"time":53990,"text":"The blood drains from her face."},{"time":56438,"text":"There are literally no words, right?"},{"time":58820,"text":"And I look at her, and I say,"},{"time":59839,"text":"\"Now, don't you think we need"},{"time":61729,"text":"more than one black person in the U.S. Senate?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":65800,"text":"Now Harold and I --"},{"time":67828,"text":"(Applause) â€”"},{"time":70346,"text":"we still laugh about that story,"},{"time":73435,"text":"and in many ways, the moment caught me off guard,"},{"time":76871,"text":"but deep, deep down inside,"},{"time":79891,"text":"I actually wasn't surprised."},{"time":82015,"text":"And I wasn't surprised because of something"},{"time":83438,"text":"my mother taught me about 30 years before."},{"time":86574,"text":"You see, my mother was ruthlessly realistic."},{"time":89989,"text":"I remember one day coming\nhome from a birthday party"},{"time":91981,"text":"where I was the only black kid invited,"},{"time":93820,"text":"and instead of asking me the\nnormal motherly questions"},{"time":96497,"text":"like, \"Did you have fun?\" or \"How was the cake?\""},{"time":99481,"text":"my mother looked at me and she said,"},{"time":101658,"text":"\"How did they treat you?\""},{"time":103890,"text":"I was seven. I did not understand."},{"time":106657,"text":"I mean, why would anyone treat me differently?"},{"time":109940,"text":"But she knew."},{"time":111065,"text":"And she looked me right in the eye and she said,"},{"time":113737,"text":"\"They will not always treat you well.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":116912,"text":"Now, race is one of those topics in America"},{"time":119258,"text":"that makes people extraordinarily uncomfortable."},{"time":122736,"text":"You bring it up at a dinner party"},{"time":124390,"text":"or in a workplace environment,"},{"time":126035,"text":"it is literally the conversational equivalent"},{"time":129215,"text":"of touching the third rail."},{"time":131090,"text":"There is shock,"},{"time":132265,"text":"followed by a long silence."},{"time":135230,"text":"And even coming here today,"},{"time":136884,"text":"I told some friends and colleagues"},{"time":138035,"text":"that I planned to talk about race,"},{"time":139601,"text":"and they warned me, they told me, don't do it,"},{"time":142260,"text":"that there'd be huge risks"},{"time":144147,"text":"in me talking about this topic,"},{"time":145677,"text":"that people might think I'm a militant black woman"},{"time":148168,"text":"and I would ruin my career."},{"time":150352,"text":"And I have to tell you,"},{"time":151643,"text":"I actually for a moment was a bit afraid."},{"time":154100,"text":"Then I realized,"},{"time":156170,"text":"the first step to solving any problem"},{"time":158649,"text":"is to not hide from it,"},{"time":160440,"text":"and the first step to any form of action"},{"time":164422,"text":"is awareness."},{"time":166477,"text":"And so I decided to actually talk about race."},{"time":169917,"text":"And I decided that if I came\nhere and shared with you"},{"time":172790,"text":"some of my experiences,"},{"time":174974,"text":"that maybe we could all be a little less anxious"},{"time":177662,"text":"and a little more bold"},{"time":179208,"text":"in our conversations about race."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182110,"text":"Now I know there are people out there who will say"},{"time":184100,"text":"that the election of Barack Obama meant"},{"time":185726,"text":"that it was the end of racial discrimination"},{"time":188525,"text":"for all eternity, right?"},{"time":190547,"text":"But I work in the investment business,"},{"time":192190,"text":"and we have a saying:"},{"time":193650,"text":"The numbers do not lie."},{"time":195705,"text":"And here, there are significant,"},{"time":198319,"text":"quantifiable racial disparities"},{"time":201040,"text":"that cannot be ignored,"},{"time":202559,"text":"in household wealth, household income,"},{"time":206142,"text":"job opportunities, healthcare."},{"time":209141,"text":"One example from corporate America:"},{"time":211628,"text":"Even though white men"},{"time":213633,"text":"make up just 30 percent of the U.S. population,"},{"time":217424,"text":"they hold 70 percent of all corporate board seats."},{"time":221823,"text":"Of the Fortune 250,"},{"time":224101,"text":"there are only seven CEOs that are minorities,"},{"time":227944,"text":"and of the thousands of publicly\ntraded companies today, thousands,"},{"time":232210,"text":"only two are chaired by black women,"},{"time":235036,"text":"and you're looking at one of them,"},{"time":236841,"text":"the same one who, not too long ago,"},{"time":238993,"text":"was nearly mistaken for kitchen help."},{"time":241850,"text":"So that is a fact."},{"time":243024,"text":"Now I have this thought experiment"},{"time":245212,"text":"that I play with myself, when I say,"},{"time":247739,"text":"imagine if I walked you into a room"},{"time":249998,"text":"and it was of a major corporation, like ExxonMobil,"},{"time":253257,"text":"and every single person around\nthe boardroom were black,"},{"time":256867,"text":"you would think that were weird."},{"time":259400,"text":"But if I walked you into a Fortune 500 company,"},{"time":262204,"text":"and everyone around the table is a white male,"},{"time":264327,"text":"when will it be that we think that's weird too?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267426,"text":"And I know how we got here."},{"time":269140,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":273303,"text":"I know how we got here."},{"time":275071,"text":"You know, there was institutionalized,"},{"time":277757,"text":"at one time legalized, discrimination in our country."},{"time":280866,"text":"There's no question about it."},{"time":283160,"text":"But still, as I grapple with this issue,"},{"time":285985,"text":"my mother's question hangs in the air for me:"},{"time":288510,"text":"How did they treat you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":290593,"text":"Now, I do not raise this issue to complain"},{"time":293069,"text":"or in any way to elicit any kind of sympathy."},{"time":295315,"text":"I have succeeded in my life"},{"time":297298,"text":"beyond my wildest expectations,"},{"time":300140,"text":"and I have been treated well by people of all races"},{"time":303105,"text":"more often than I have not."},{"time":305341,"text":"I tell the uniform story because it happened."},{"time":308154,"text":"I cite those statistics around\ncorporate board diversity"},{"time":310774,"text":"because they are real,"},{"time":312438,"text":"and I stand here today"},{"time":314102,"text":"talking about this issue of racial discrimination"},{"time":316692,"text":"because I believe it threatens to rob"},{"time":319187,"text":"another generation of all the opportunities"},{"time":322473,"text":"that all of us want for all of our children,"},{"time":325058,"text":"no matter what their color"},{"time":326821,"text":"or where they come from."},{"time":328620,"text":"And I think it also threatens to hold back businesses."},{"time":332198,"text":"You see, researchers have coined this term"},{"time":334999,"text":"\"color blindness\""},{"time":336834,"text":"to describe a learned behavior where we pretend"},{"time":339509,"text":"that we don't notice race."},{"time":341354,"text":"If you happen to be surrounded by a bunch of people"},{"time":343514,"text":"who look like you, that's purely accidental."},{"time":347290,"text":"Now, color blindness, in my view,"},{"time":349390,"text":"doesn't mean that there's no racial discrimination,"},{"time":352248,"text":"and there's fairness."},{"time":353943,"text":"It doesn't mean that at all. It doesn't ensure it."},{"time":356090,"text":"In my view, color blindness is very dangerous"},{"time":358488,"text":"because it means we're ignoring the problem."},{"time":361245,"text":"There was a corporate study that said that,"},{"time":363775,"text":"instead of avoiding race,"},{"time":365552,"text":"the really smart corporations\nactually deal with it head on."},{"time":369524,"text":"They actually recognize that embracing diversity"},{"time":372308,"text":"means recognizing all races,"},{"time":375307,"text":"including the majority one."},{"time":377669,"text":"But I'll be the first one to tell you,"},{"time":379465,"text":"this subject matter can be hard,"},{"time":382306,"text":"awkward, uncomfortable -- but that's kind of the point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386358,"text":"In the spirit of debunking racial stereotypes,"},{"time":389380,"text":"the one that black people don't like to swim,"},{"time":391555,"text":"I'm going to tell you how much I love to swim."},{"time":394785,"text":"I love to swim so much"},{"time":397072,"text":"that as an adult, I swim with a coach."},{"time":399204,"text":"And one day my coach had me do a drill"},{"time":402041,"text":"where I had to swim to one end of a 25-meter pool"},{"time":404652,"text":"without taking a breath."},{"time":406540,"text":"And every single time I failed,"},{"time":408681,"text":"I had to start over."},{"time":410018,"text":"And I failed a lot."},{"time":411531,"text":"By the end, I got it, but when I got out of the pool,"},{"time":413398,"text":"I was exasperated and tired and annoyed,"},{"time":416021,"text":"and I said, \"Why are we doing\nbreath-holding exercises?\""},{"time":419959,"text":"And my coach looked me\nat me, and he said, \"Mellody,"},{"time":422125,"text":"that was not a breath-holding exercise."},{"time":425116,"text":"That drill was to make you comfortable"},{"time":427465,"text":"being uncomfortable,"},{"time":429258,"text":"because that's how most of us spend our days.\""},{"time":432389,"text":"If we can learn to deal with our discomfort,"},{"time":434655,"text":"and just relax into it,"},{"time":436689,"text":"we'll have a better life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438913,"text":"So I think it's time for us to be comfortable"},{"time":441466,"text":"with the uncomfortable conversation about race:"},{"time":444712,"text":"black, white, Asian, Hispanic,"},{"time":447388,"text":"male, female, all of us,"},{"time":449661,"text":"if we truly believe in equal rights"},{"time":451937,"text":"and equal opportunity in America,"},{"time":453948,"text":"I think we have to have real conversations"},{"time":456951,"text":"about this issue."},{"time":458203,"text":"We cannot afford to be color blind."},{"time":460975,"text":"We have to be color brave."},{"time":464222,"text":"We have to be willing, as teachers and parents"},{"time":468260,"text":"and entrepreneurs and scientists,"},{"time":470090,"text":"we have to be willing to have"},{"time":471373,"text":"proactive conversations about race"},{"time":474210,"text":"with honesty and understanding and courage,"},{"time":477349,"text":"not because it's the right thing to do,"},{"time":480888,"text":"but because it's the smart thing to do,"},{"time":483161,"text":"because our businesses and our products"},{"time":485544,"text":"and our science, our research,"},{"time":487598,"text":"all of that will be better with greater diversity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491235,"text":"Now, my favorite example of color bravery"},{"time":494190,"text":"is a guy named John Skipper."},{"time":495648,"text":"He runs ESPN."},{"time":497500,"text":"He's a North Carolina native,"},{"time":499830,"text":"quintessential Southern gentleman, white."},{"time":502877,"text":"He joined ESPN, which already had a culture"},{"time":505288,"text":"of inclusion and diversity, but he took it up a notch."},{"time":508061,"text":"He demanded that every open position"},{"time":510649,"text":"have a diverse slate of candidates."},{"time":513599,"text":"Now he says the senior people"},{"time":515398,"text":"in the beginning bristled,"},{"time":517210,"text":"and they would come to him and say,"},{"time":519260,"text":"\"Do you want me to hire the minority,"},{"time":521868,"text":"or do you want me to hire\nthe best person for the job?\""},{"time":525486,"text":"And Skipper says his answers were always the same:"},{"time":529145,"text":"\"Yes.\""},{"time":530820,"text":"And by saying yes to diversity,"},{"time":532630,"text":"I honestly believe that ESPN"},{"time":534992,"text":"is the most valuable cable franchise in the world."},{"time":537482,"text":"I think that's a part of the secret sauce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539928,"text":"Now I can tell you, in my own industry,"},{"time":541970,"text":"at Ariel Investments, we actually view our diversity"},{"time":544145,"text":"as a competitive advantage,"},{"time":546305,"text":"and that advantage can extend\nway beyond business."},{"time":549626,"text":"There's a guy named Scott Page\nat the University of Michigan."},{"time":551810,"text":"He is the first person to develop"},{"time":553539,"text":"a mathematical calculation for diversity."},{"time":556579,"text":"He says, if you're trying to\nsolve a really hard problem,"},{"time":558870,"text":"really hard,"},{"time":560031,"text":"that you should have a diverse group of people,"},{"time":562860,"text":"including those with diverse intellects."},{"time":565870,"text":"The example that he gives is the smallpox epidemic."},{"time":568723,"text":"When it was ravaging Europe,"},{"time":571648,"text":"they brought together all these scientists,"},{"time":573028,"text":"and they were stumped."},{"time":574490,"text":"And the beginnings of the cure to the disease"},{"time":577582,"text":"came from the most unlikely source,"},{"time":579775,"text":"a dairy farmer who noticed that the milkmaids"},{"time":584155,"text":"were not getting smallpox."},{"time":586064,"text":"And the smallpox vaccination is bovine-based"},{"time":589418,"text":"because of that dairy farmer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591820,"text":"Now I'm sure you're sitting here and you're saying,"},{"time":594232,"text":"I don't run a cable company,"},{"time":596327,"text":"I don't run an investment firm,"},{"time":598449,"text":"I am not a dairy farmer."},{"time":599900,"text":"What can I do?"},{"time":601350,"text":"And I'm telling you, you can be color brave."},{"time":604866,"text":"If you're part of a hiring process"},{"time":606750,"text":"or an admissions process,"},{"time":608390,"text":"you can be color brave."},{"time":610057,"text":"If you are trying to solve a really hard problem,"},{"time":612901,"text":"you can speak up and be color brave."},{"time":615680,"text":"Now I know people will say,"},{"time":618929,"text":"but that doesn't add up to a lot,"},{"time":621079,"text":"but I'm actually asking you\nto do something really simple:"},{"time":624050,"text":"observe your environment,"},{"time":626268,"text":"at work, at school, at home."},{"time":630080,"text":"I'm asking you to look at the people around you"},{"time":632429,"text":"purposefully and intentionally."},{"time":635050,"text":"Invite people into your life"},{"time":636493,"text":"who don't look like you, don't think like you,"},{"time":639329,"text":"don't act like you,"},{"time":640624,"text":"don't come from where you come from,"},{"time":642585,"text":"and you might find that they\nwill challenge your assumptions"},{"time":645235,"text":"and make you grow as a person."},{"time":646991,"text":"You might get powerful new insights"},{"time":649331,"text":"from these individuals,"},{"time":650954,"text":"or, like my husband, who happens to be white,"},{"time":654140,"text":"you might learn that black people,"},{"time":656210,"text":"men, women, children,"},{"time":657767,"text":"we use body lotion every single day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660656,"text":"Now, I also think that this is very important"},{"time":665278,"text":"so that the next generation really understands"},{"time":668250,"text":"that this progress will help them,"},{"time":669760,"text":"because they're expecting\nus to be great role models."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672894,"text":"Now, I told you, my mother,"},{"time":674371,"text":"she was ruthlessly realistic."},{"time":675942,"text":"She was an unbelievable role model."},{"time":679182,"text":"She was the kind of person"},{"time":680313,"text":"who got to be the way she was"},{"time":681635,"text":"because she was a single mom"},{"time":683611,"text":"with six kids in Chicago."},{"time":685283,"text":"She was in the real estate business,"},{"time":687075,"text":"where she worked extraordinarily hard"},{"time":689825,"text":"but oftentimes had a hard time making ends meet."},{"time":693093,"text":"And that meant sometimes we got"},{"time":694940,"text":"our phone disconnected,"},{"time":696320,"text":"or our lights turned off,"},{"time":697188,"text":"or we got evicted."},{"time":699129,"text":"When we got evicted, sometimes we lived"},{"time":700670,"text":"in these small apartments that she owned,"},{"time":702476,"text":"sometimes in only one or two rooms,"},{"time":704075,"text":"because they weren't completed,"},{"time":705832,"text":"and we would heat our bathwater on hot plates."},{"time":710543,"text":"But she never gave up hope, ever,"},{"time":713055,"text":"and she never allowed us to give up hope either."},{"time":715735,"text":"This brutal pragmatism that she had,"},{"time":717312,"text":"I mean, I was four and she told me,"},{"time":719106,"text":"\"Mommy is Santa.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":721429,"text":"She was this brutal pragmatism."},{"time":723912,"text":"She taught me so many lessons,"},{"time":726285,"text":"but the most important lesson"},{"time":728118,"text":"was that every single day she told me,"},{"time":731344,"text":"\"Mellody, you can be anything.\""},{"time":736680,"text":"And because of those words,"},{"time":738538,"text":"I would wake up at the crack of dawn,"},{"time":740643,"text":"and because of those words,"},{"time":742459,"text":"I would love school more than anything,"},{"time":745471,"text":"and because of those words, when I was on a bus"},{"time":747404,"text":"going to school, I dreamed the biggest dreams."},{"time":750657,"text":"And it's because of those words\nthat I stand here right now"},{"time":753760,"text":"full of passion,"},{"time":755716,"text":"asking you to be brave for the kids"},{"time":758124,"text":"who are dreaming those dreams today."},{"time":760434,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":765855,"text":"You see, I want them to look at a CEO on television"},{"time":770044,"text":"and say, \"I can be like her,\""},{"time":772231,"text":"or, \"He looks like me.\""},{"time":774738,"text":"And I want them to know"},{"time":776479,"text":"that anything is possible,"},{"time":778174,"text":"that they can achieve the highest level"},{"time":779690,"text":"that they ever imagined,"},{"time":781444,"text":"that they will be welcome\nin any corporate boardroom,"},{"time":784539,"text":"or they can lead any company."},{"time":787430,"text":"You see this idea of being the land"},{"time":789368,"text":"of the free and the home of the brave,"},{"time":791042,"text":"it's woven into the fabric of America."},{"time":794490,"text":"America, when we have a challenge,"},{"time":796498,"text":"we take it head on, we don't shrink away from it."},{"time":799374,"text":"We take a stand. We show courage."},{"time":802233,"text":"So right now, what I'm asking you to do,"},{"time":804242,"text":"I'm asking you to show courage."},{"time":806220,"text":"I'm asking you to be bold."},{"time":808488,"text":"As business leaders, I'm asking you"},{"time":810309,"text":"not to leave anything on the table."},{"time":812512,"text":"As citizens, I'm asking you\nnot to leave any child behind."},{"time":816552,"text":"I'm asking you not to be color blind,"},{"time":819007,"text":"but to be color brave,"},{"time":821110,"text":"so that every child knows that their future matters"},{"time":824267,"text":"and their dreams are possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825899,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828429,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":833917,"text":"Thank you. Thanks. Thanks. (Applause)"}]}]}